comments: Valanciunas (MEM) firms up in his screening position in Dotson's (CLE) path and does not deliver the contact.
Valanciunas (MEM) establishes himself in a screening position in Okoro's (CLE) path and does not deliver the contact.
Valanciunas (MEM) and Drummond (CLE) engage and disengage with one another in the lane.
Valanciunas (MEM) makes clean contact with the ball and it becomes dislodged prior to incidental contact taking place with Drummond (CLE) during rebounding.
Valanciunas (MEM) moves laterally and delivers contact to Drummond's (CLE) side that affects his driving shot attempt.
Drummond (CLE) swipes down and makes contact across Jones' (MEM) left arm during the driving shot attempt.
Jones (MEM) swipes forward and makes a slight brush with Drummond's (CLE) right wrist at the end of the drive.
Valanciunas (MEM) is in a legal guarding position when marginal body contact occurs with Drummond (CLE) in the lane, which Valanciunas absorbs.
Valanciunas (MEM) uses his leg to dislodge the ball from Drummond (CLE).  Following the whistle, Valanciunas (MEM) inadvertently makes contact with Drummond.
Brooks (MEM) and Osman (CLE) engage and disengage with one another off-ball.
Anderson (MEM) reaches in and makes clean contact with the ball as Drummond (CLE) dribbles near the free throw line.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Drummond (CLE) touches the ball last before it goes out of bounds.
Anderson (MEM) slides his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Nance Jr. (CLE) makes marginal contact with Anderson's (MEM) side as Anderson starts his dribble.
Dotson (CLE) has his hand rested on Jones' (MEM) front and marginal contact occurs as Jones passes the ball.
Dotson (CLE) jumps to the side of Brooks (MEM) and would have avoid making contact with him if Brooks hadn't extended his left foot to the side.
Valanciunas (MEM) delivers body contact to Drummond (CLE) after his gather.

As Osman (CLE) returns to the floor during the rebound, his left arm extends outward to brace for contact and some occurs with Anderson's (MEM) head/neck area. Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Drummond (CLE) reaches in and makes clean contact with the ball before incidental contact occurs with Brooks (MEM).
Nance Jr. (CLE) and Brooks (MEM) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
